m from school (1300- 1400m ASL).\r\n\r\nGrey Wagtail: About 10 individuals within the campus.  There seems to be about 1 bird to every building on the campus, sometimes in pairs.  Usually seen on the ground but flies to the top of the roof (Tiled mostly) when approached by humans.  One individual is regularly seen foraging in the open drain behind the Dining hall.\r\n\r\nBrown Shrike:1 or 2 individuals seen on campus.  Prefers open spaces at the edge of bush or lantana covered areas.  Usually seen perched on a fence post, seems to prefer certain posts to others.  Usually silent during the day but has been seen making calls in the evenings (around 6:00PM).\r\n\r\nGreenish warbler:  We are uncertain about the identification of the warbler due to presence of some other warbler species.  the calls were certainly of help but even here there seems to be some variations.  Ususally single individuals flitting from branch to branch of trees with dense, thick growth, accompanied with the sharp whistle like call (Tswee...) in frequencies of about one call to a second.  Very difficult to sight clearly.\r\n','2007-12-04 05:35:17','Sholai School'),(321,'V. Santharam','birds@rishivalley.org','','Andhra Pradesh','Madanapalle','Chittoor','','','2007-08-01','Daily','0000-00-00','0000-00-00','0000-00-00','0000-00-00','2007-09-02','2007-10-12','0000-00-00','2007-09-01','2007-11-24','I was away for a few days from mid-October and also in mid-November.','2007-12-04 08:56:23','Rishi Valley'),(322,'Bhargav Joshi','bhargavjoshi_1978@yahoo.co.in','','Gujarat','Vadodara','Vadodara','22.18','73.15','2007-11-01','Weekly','0000-00-00','0000-00-00','0000-00-00','0000-00-00','2007-11-08','0000-00-00','0000-00-00','0000-00-00','2007-11-04','','2007-12-04 09:47:56','Vadodara'),(323,'Bhargav Joshi','bhargavjoshi_1978@yahoo.co.in','','Gujarat','Sri Por timbi','Vadodara','','','2007-11-01','Fortnightly','0000-00-00','2007-12-02','0000-00-00','2007-12-02','2007-12-02','0000-00-00','0000-00-00','0000-00-